19/03/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Adrian Nastase arrived in Bratislava, Slovakia on Thursday (18 March) to participate in a conference on the new agenda of an enlarged Europe.
The forum will gather heads of state, government officials and politicians from 26 European countries and the United States.
NATO Secretary General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer and EU Enlargement Commissioner Gunter Verheugen will also attend.
In other news Thursday, Romania's Environment Ministry said ten tonnes of toxic waste, including cyanide, have spilled into a river near the defunct Metadet chemical plant in Falticeni.
In 2001, a similar accident in the area poisoned fish.
(Rompres, Reuters - 18/03/04)
